---
import Section from '../../../components/core/layout/Section.astro';
import StyledList from '../../../components/core/lists/StyledList.astro';
import ContentLayout from '../../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';

import weakener from '../../../assets/rise/guides/dangos/dango_weakener.png';
import booster from '../../../assets/rise/guides/dangos/dango_booster.png';
import moxie from '../../../assets/rise/guides/dangos/dango_moxie.png';
import fighter from '../../../assets/rise/guides/dangos/dango_fighter.png';
import driver from '../../../assets/rise/guides/dangos/dango_driver.png';
import defender from '../../../assets/rise/guides/dangos/dango_defender.png';
import super_recovery from '../../../assets/rise/guides/dangos/dango_super_recovery.png';
import feet from '../../../assets/rise/guides/dangos/dango_feet.png';
import ImageGrid from '../../../components/core/media/ImageGrid.astro';
import DangoCard from '../../../components/guides/DangoCard.astro';
---

<ContentLayout>
  <Section>
    <p>
      Dango skills are a crucial part of hunt preparation in Rise. While there are many options
      available, only a handful make a meaningful impact on hunt performance. This guide focuses on
      the most effective combinations that complement lance gameplay.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section title="My Favourite Setups">
    <p>So here are my most used Dango setups:</p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <DangoCard
        title="Anomaly Investigation Setup"
        description="Balanced setup focusing on survivability and consistent damage output."
        dangos={{
          lvl4: {
            text: 'Dango Booster',
            emoji: '💪',
          },
          lvl3: {
            text: 'Dango Moxie',
            emoji: '👼',
          },
          lvl1: {
            text: 'Dango Defender',
            emoji: '🛡️',
          },
        }}
      />

      <DangoCard
        title="Dereliction Setup"
        description="Super recovery offsets health drain while maintaining offensive capabilities."
        dangos={{
          lvl4: {
            text: 'Dango Super Recovery',
            emoji: '🩹',
          },
          lvl3: {
            text: 'Dango Moxie',
            emoji: '👼',
          },
          lvl1: {
            text: 'Dango Booster',
            emoji: '💪',
          },
        }}
      />

      <DangoCard
        title="Weakener Setup"
        description="Maximizes efficiency when hosting non-Anomaly quests."
        dangos={{
          lvl4: {
            text: 'Dango Weakener',
            emoji: '🔪',
          },
          lvl3: {
            text: 'Dango Moxie',
            emoji: '👼',
          },
          lvl1: {
            text: 'Dango Booster',
            emoji: '💪',
          },
        }}
      />
    </div>

    <Section title="How To Decide Which Dango To Use">
      <p>
        Using Hopping Skewer is almost always worth it. So here's a Guide on what your Dango setup
        could look like:
      </p>

      <StyledList
        items={[
          {
            text: 'Weakener for hosted non-anomaly quests, otherwise Booster/Defender based on matchup difficulty',
            emoji: '4️⃣',
          },
          {
            text: 'Moxie for one-shot protection, Booster if confident in the matchup',
            emoji: '3️⃣',
          },
          {
            text: 'Feet for multiplayer without Flinch Free, Fighter for stamina-heavy matchups, otherwise Booster/Defender',
            emoji: '1️⃣',
          },
        ]}
      />
    </Section>

    <Section title="Which Are The Best Dangos?">
      <ImageGrid
        images={[
          {
            src: weakener,
            alt: 'Dango Weakener',
            title: 'Weakener',
            caption:
              'Forces lower monster HP values when hosting non-anomaly quests. Can reduce target monster HP by up to 10%',
          },
          {
            src: booster,
            alt: 'Booster',
            title: 'Booster',
            caption:
              'Gives 6/9/12/15 Raw and 10/15/20/30 defense at lvl 1/2/3/4. Free stat boost :)',
          },
          {
            src: moxie,
            alt: 'Moxie',
            title: 'Moxie',
            caption:
              'One-shot prevention above health threshold. Essential for challenging content, unreliable below level 3.',
          },
          {
            src: fighter,
            alt: 'Dango Fighter',
            title: 'Fighter',
            caption:
              'Reduces stamina costs for blocking and dodging. Particularly valuable for guard-heavy playstyles.',
          },
          {
            src: driver,
            alt: 'Driver',
            title: 'Driver',
            caption:
              'Increases the amount of recoverable red health when taking damage. Particularly effective with recovery skills, Bloodlust, or Strife builds.',
          },
          {
            src: defender,
            alt: 'Defender',
            title: 'Defender',
            caption:
              'Flat defense boost with chance to reduce damage. Super comfy if you get hit a lot.',
          },
          {
            src: super_recovery,
            alt: 'Super Recovery',
            title: 'Super Recovery',
            caption:
              'Gradual health regeneration. Primarily used to offset Dereliction/Berserk drain, requires level 4 for meaningful impact.',
          },
          {
            src: feet,
            alt: 'Feet',
            title: 'Feet',
            caption:
              'Grants Flinch Free at level 1. Essential for multiplayer if not slotted in armor.',
          },
        ]}
      />
    </Section>
  </Section>
</ContentLayout>
